  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Cross Border Peace and Strengthening Sustainable Livelihoods of Cattle Herders and Crop Farmers in Sierra Leone and Guinea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the application of innovative and inclusive approaches to conflict mediation and cross-border communication, this project aims to strengthen the relationship between Guinea and Sierra Leone by addressing recurring cross-border conflicts occurring between cattle herders and farmers. Support will be provided to border communities in the Falaba district (Sierra Leone) and Faranah prefecture (Guinea) to ensure that they benefit from more accountable institutions, together with mechanisms that facilitate and improve cross-border relations which will in turn promote peaceful co-existence. This project also strengthens social cohesion between the Falaba District of Sierra Leone and the Faranah Prefecture of Guinea by supporting climate-smart livelihoods and overall herder and farmer cooperation.</narrative>
  </description>
